SIMPLE: stithy
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stithy
<hw>Stith"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Stith</er>,
and cf. <er>Stiddy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An anvil.</def>
<rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A smith's shop; a smithy; a smithery; a forge.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧As foul as Vulcan's <xex>stithy</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stithy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stithy
<hw>Stith"y</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To forge on an anvil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The forge that <qex>stithied</qex> Mars his helm.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stive</ent>⟦br⟧
